=== Analysis ===
1. The time delay e^(-tau*s) adds phase lag to the open-loop system.
   This reduces the phase margin and can cause instability.

2. Pade approximation converts the delay into a rational transfer function.
   Higher-order approximations are more accurate but increase system order.

3. Smith predictor principle:
   An internal plant model G_hat(s) and delay model e^(-tau_hat*s) are used
   to "remove" the delay from the feedback loop.
   The resulting closed-loop has the characteristic equation 1 + C(s)G(s) = 0,
   which is independent of the time delay.
   The delay only appears in the numerator: G_cl = C*G*e^(-tau*s)/(1 + C*G).

4. Smith predictor effectively recovers the undelayed response shape,
   shifted by the time delay tau.
