====== Analysis Summary ======
1. Regular feedback with time delay:
   - Delay introduces phase lag in the loop
   - Can cause oscillation or instability
   - Step response shows delayed reaction and overshoot

2. Smith Predictor:
   - Uses internal model Gm(s) to predict undelayed output
   - Subtracts delayed model prediction, adds instantaneous prediction
   - Controller effectively "sees" delay-free plant
   - Result: response matches ideal case, shifted by tau

